The movie is outstanding but I watched it once after setting the correct region and I can't get it to play again. I get a pop up box that tells me that the movie is in zone 1 (the correct zone) and would I like to change it but if I hit cancel, ore just close the box or even try to reset the zone, it will not let me and the disc automatically ejects. So, I spent over 20 bucks to rent a movie for one viewing.
Simply one of the great performances by at least three great actors and an illumination of the life and career of one of the truly great innovators in rock and roll.  All hail, Jerry Lee.
Returned because the movie kept freezing up. Poor quality.

Great music and great acting by all.  Although, considered by most to be only a movie, and made primarily for entertainment only, I also consider it to be valuable documentary.  Why?  Because it preserves the historical contribution of Jerry Lee Lewis to music, and especially to Rock and Roll.  Elvis was great but I have always thought Jerry Lee Lewis was the King, just my personal opinion.
